Description: Fragment of foot of East Greek pottery vessel; probably from a pedestal for a krater; lipped, vertical edge. Slipped on top with brown-fired band, with added red line, at outside, extending a little over edge.
Curator's comments: The form of foot is a smaller version of that of the Protarchos krater, 1886,0401.830.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.954)
